# Performance System

Performance is a core product feature.

LexMastery must feel instant.

---

# Product Vision

Performance system must:

- ensure fast startup
- optimize rendering
- minimize memory usage
- reduce API load
- guarantee smooth UX

---

# Architecture

PerformanceController

↓

PerformanceState

↓

CacheManager

↓

LazyLoader

↓

Resource Optimizer

---

# Rendering Rules

- avoid full widget rebuilds
- use lazy rendering everywhere
- paginate large lists
- defer heavy computations

---

# Caching Strategy

Cache layers:

1. Memory cache (fast)
2. Local storage cache (persistent)
3. Remote cache (fallback)

---

# Data Loading Strategy

- eager load critical UI
- lazy load secondary data
- prefetch next likely content

---

# AI Performance Rules

- stream responses
- cancel stale requests
- cache frequent queries
- reuse embeddings

---

# Offline Optimization

- prioritize cached content
- disable heavy AI features offline
- preload essential modules

---

# API Performance Rules

- batch requests
- compress payloads
- debounce calls
- avoid redundant fetches

---

# State Optimization

- minimize rebuild triggers
- split state into granular units
- avoid global re-renders

---

# Performance Budgets

- app startup: <2s
- screen load: <200ms
- AI first token: <500ms
- search response: <300ms

---

# Memory Management

- dispose unused controllers
- clear unused caches
- limit in-memory history size

---

# Testing Requirements

Unit Tests:

Cache logic

Lazy loading system

Performance thresholds

Integration Tests:

Full app load performance

